## Decisions & deviations — THE ONLY RECORD OF MID-BUILD DEVIATION IN THIS PROJECT

**NEVER ARCHIVE, PRUNE, SUMMARIZE, OR "TIDY" THIS SECTION. NOT AT A PHASE BOUNDARY. NOT EVER.**

This tier has no `docs-sync`, so **nothing writes a deviation back into `{{DESIGN}}`.** `story-scoper` reads the design as ground truth for every brief, and this section is the *only* place it can learn that the design has been superseded. It is instructed to read this section before writing every brief, and to let an entry here **beat the design text**.

Delete a line from here and the fact it recorded exists nowhere. Every later brief then quotes a superseded spec with total confidence, the engineer builds it, and the reviewer passes it — because all three are reading the same stale design and nothing contradicts it. This is the sharpest failure mode this tier has, and it is silent.

The trade is deliberate: no fold cycle, no archive split, no epic gate — a shorter build. It holds while the ledger is short.

**If this ledger passes ~25 entries, the tier was wrong.** Regenerate at `full`, which folds deviations into the design at each epic gate (`docs-sync`) so the scoper reads them from the design itself. Do not hand-bolt that gate on here.

Keep every entry to **one concrete line** an engineer could build against. Tag it with the story that produced it.

- **<STORY-ID>**: <the decision future stories must respect, stated concretely enough to build against>.

