### Repair stories (from a RED `regression-run` — NOT in `{{PLAN}}`; run first, must clear before the phase gate closes)

Each is minted from a **numbered** finding in `regression-run`'s return. The orchestrator holds that return in context and pastes the finding's text straight into the scoper's dispatch prompt — **it never opens the report file.** Record the finding's report + number here only as an audit trail; the acceptance criteria travel in the dispatch prompt, not through this line.

- `[pending]` **R-<N>.1** <one-line title> — from `regression-<PHASE>-r1.md` finding #3
- `[done]` **R-<N>.2** <one-line title> — from `regression-<PHASE>-r1.md` finding #1 — commit `<hash>`

(empty if none)

**Termination bound:** if the same failing test survives two repair → `regression-run` cycles, **stop**. Mark it `blocked`, record every repair tried and why each did not clear it. Two failed attempts at the same red means the diagnosis is wrong, and a third repair will not find it.

